sentences: Margaret Valiant (February 22, 1901 – April 11, 1982) was an American musician, folklorist, ethnomusicologist and activist.
Margaret Valiant was born on February 22, 1901 in Como, Panola County, Mississippi to Denton Hurlock Brahan and Johnnie C. Everson Brahan.
Valiant moved to Memphis in 1914 after the death of her cousin.
Valiant graduated from Central High School in 1918.
She studied piano in Memphis and continued her studies at the Cincinnati Conservatory where she received a degree in music in 1922.
